decks.notes: This deck focuses on generating value through card advantage, tempo plays, and control elements. It aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan with a mix of removal spells, counterspells, and efficient creatures. The inclusion of Yorion as a companion allows for extra value through blinking permanents. The deck also takes advantage of powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler and Wrenn and Six to control the board and generate incremental advantage. The mana base is carefully constructed to support the deck's color requirements and maximize consistency.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by utilizing a combination of removal spells, card draw, and powerful creatures. The key strategy is to efficiently ramp up mana using powerful lands like Omnath, Locus of Creation and Risen Reef, while keeping the opponent's board in check with cards like Unholy Heat and Teferi, Time Raveler. The deck also utilizes Elemental synergies to generate value and advantage over time. Yorion, Sky Nomad serves as a powerful companion that can reset the battlefield and provide card advantage.

The main strategy of this deck is to quickly deploy aggressive threats such as Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Dragon's Rage Channeler while disrupting the opponent with counter spells and removal like Lightning Bolt and Unholy Heat. The deck also includes card draw and selection spells like Mishra's Bauble and Consider to maintain card advantage and find key pieces. The mana base is optimized to support the deck's color requirements and ensure consistent deployment of threats and answers. Overall, the deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain control throughout the game.

The deck focuses on utilizing the Amulet of Vigor to generate extra mana and play Primeval Titan as quickly as possible. By utilizing lands that can tap for multiple mana along with bouncing lands back to hand, the deck can easily generate the necessary resources to put multiple powerful threats onto the battlefield in a single turn. The key strategy revolves around ramping up quickly and overwhelming the opponent with large creatures and powerful land interactions.

This deck focuses on assembling a toolbox of creatures that can be searched for and put into play using cards like Chord of Calling and Eldritch Evolution. The key strategy is to use Yawgmoth, Thran Physician's ability to generate value by sacrificing creatures and drawing cards, while also utilizing Grist, the Hunger Tide to create insect tokens and fuel the combo. Blood Artist provides a win condition by draining the opponent's life whenever creatures die, and Geralf's Messenger can also chip away at their life total. The deck aims to outvalue and overwhelm the opponent with its versatile creature selection and combo potential.

The deck focuses on aggressively playing low cost creatures and spells to quickly apply pressure on the opponent. Using efficient counterspells and removal, it aims to control the board while consistently drawing cards and managing resources effectively. The deck's synergy lies in its ability to quickly adapt to different situations and minimize the opponent's options through tempo manipulation and card advantage. With a mix of evasion, card selection, and disruption, it aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure victory through a combination of early aggression and card advantage.

This UW Control deck focuses on utilizing counterspells, removal, and planeswalkers to control the game and disrupt the opponent's strategy. By consistently countering threats and removing key permanents, the deck aims to outvalue the opponent and eventually win the game through card advantage and control. The inclusion of a companion like Kaheera adds an additional layer of synergy and strategy to the deck. The mana base is optimized to support the deck's ability to play multiple colors and cast its spells efficiently.

The deck focuses on control through a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler and Wrenn and Six. It also utilizes the companion mechanic with Yorion, Sky Nomad for additional value. The deck aims to control the board and outvalue the opponent through card advantage and incremental advantages. It also includes a toolbox of cards like Traverse the Ulvenwald to find specific answers and threats when needed. The mana base is carefully crafted to support the deck's requirements and ensure consistent casting of spells.

The deck focuses on controlling the game by using a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and card advantage. It utilizes Yorion, Sky Nomad as a companion to provide additional value and flexibility. The deck aims to control the board and slow down the opponent's strategy while building up its own resources. The key strategy is to establish a board presence with powerful creatures like Omnath, Locus of Creation and then using cards like Time Warp to take extra turns and generate advantage. The deck also includes various fetch lands and dual lands to ensure consistent mana fixing and smooth gameplay.
